potatoes to prepared baking sheet, toss with oil and salt and set aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Peppered Parmesan Sauce"},{"content":"Place Parmesan, peppercorns and thyme into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place shallots and butter into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>5 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chicken stock, brandy and flour and without measuring cup cook <b>10 min\/212°F\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved Parmesan mixture and whipping cream and cook <b>3 min\/195°F\/speed 2.5<b>. Meanwhile, preheat oven to broil. Transfer sauce to a bowl and set aside to keep warm."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Place reserved steamed potatoes into oven and broil until crispy (approx. 6-10 min.). Meanwhile, cook steaks."},{"content":"In a skillet over medium-high heat, add oil and cook reserved seasoned steaks. Sear 2½ minutes and flip, add butter and sear other side 2½ minutes or to your liking. Turn and sear edges (approx. 1 min. per edge)."},{"content":"When steaks are done, cover with foil and let rest 5 minutes. When potatoes are done, smash them with spatula and sprinkle with Roquefort cheese and rosemary."},{"content":"Serve steaks with Peppered Parmesan Sauce and smashed Roquefort Potatoes on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a complete meal, serve with a fresh garden salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","50m","2 portions"]}